{The great success of the Olympic Summer Games attracted many sports. 126
events took place in the eighth installment, Paris 1924.   Participation had a
great appeal to chess organizers. Pierre Vincent of France invited national
federations to Paris. A maximum of four players was allowed per country.
Participants got no money at all. So the professionals did not play.   54 men
and one woman from 18 countries had arrived in Majestic Hotel on 12 July 1924.
Strick van Linschoten withdrew and the remaining peoples could start in nine
groups of six players. Alekhine was the tournament director. The nine winners
began in the final on the evening of 15 vii. The rest continued in the
consolation group.} 1. d4 c5 2. d5 d6 3. c4 e5 4. e4 f5 $5 ({Known is} 4... g6)
