{Four usual characteristics of chess Olympiads were present at the first one:
1. The team tournament was the main event. 2. National teams of four players
met. 3. Professionals were allowed. 4. Challenge trophy became the golden
Hamilton Russell Cup.   The national federations had to pay the costs for
their teams. Sixteen countries met at the Central Hall of Westminster in
London from 18 until 30 July 1927. All played all. The country scores
consisted of the accumulated board points. Six teams had one reserve.} 1. e4 c5
2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 d6 6. Be2 e6 7. O-O Be7 8. Kh1 O-O 9.
Be3 a6 10. f4 Qc7 11. Qe1 Bd7 $5 {They play the Scheveningen.} ({Known is} 
11... Na5 {(Romanovsky - Ilyin Zhenevsky, Moscow 1925).}) 12. Qg3 Rac8 13. Rad1
Rfd8 14. e5 $1 Nd5 $2 ({Correct is} 14... dxe5 $1 15. fxe5 Nxe5 16. Bf4 Bd6 17.
Nxe6 Bxe6 18. Rxd6 Ng6 19. Rxd8+ Qxd8 {and Black will not be overwhelmed.}) 15.
Nxd5 $2 (15. Nf5 $1 g6 (15... exf5 16. Nxd5) 16. Nh6+ Kg7 17. Rxd5 {
decides the game at once.}) 15... exd5 16. Nxc6 bxc6 $2 {
White gets a second opportunity.} ({Right is} 16... Qxc6 17. Bd4 dxe5 18. Bxe5
$5 f6 $1) 17. Bd4 Bf8 ({Or} 17... g6 18. f5 $1 c5 19. e6 $1 cxd4 20. exd7) 18.
f5 c5 19. exd6 Qxd6 20. Be5 Qc6 21. Bxg7 $1 {
Britain defeated Switzerland by 3-1. Hungary crushed strong Yugoslavia by 4-0.}
1-0

