were supported by the Minister of Propaganda.   FIDE-members were allowed to
participate without racial restrictions.   The event lasted from 17 August
until 1 September. Twenty-one teams consisted of eight players and two
reserves. Aryans and Jews had a good time.  Nottingham 1936 happened at the
same time, so the British and US teams plus some great players from other
countries were active in England.} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 Be7 5.
