Qxe5 15. Bxd7+ Kxd7 16. Qd3 d4 {
will bring a balanced position in Chandler - Vaganian, Naestved 1985.}) 14. Bg5
$6 ({Preferable is} 14. Bxc6 $1 Nxc6 15. Re1 {
and White has a plus (after Fischer).}) 14... Nxe5 $1 15. Nxe5 (15. Bxd7+ Rxd7
16. Nxe5 Qxe5 17. Bxe7 Rh8 $1 18. Rae1 Rxh7 19. Rxe5 Rxe7 {(Fischer)} 20. Rd1 {
(Hübner) leads to mutual chances.}) 15... Bxb5 16. Nxf7 Bxf1 $1 17. Nxd8 Rxg5
18. Nxe6 Rxg2+ 19. Kh1 $1 ({The dangerous} 19. Kxf1 $6 Rxh2 20. Qf7 Rh1+ 21.
Kg2 Qh2+ 22. Kf3 Qh3+ 23. Kf4 Qh4+ 24. Ke5 Qh8+ 25. Kd6 Rxa1 26. Qxe7 Kb8 {
(Hübner)} 27. a6 $1 Rb1 28. Nc5 {gives a white escape.}) 19... Qe5 20. Rxf1
Qxe6 $1 21. Kxg2 Qg4+ {Tal delivers perpetual check.   The Soviets defeated
