8. Be3 Qb4 $6 9. f3 Ne5 $6 10. Bd2 $1 Qb6 11. f4 $1 Ng6 12. Bd3 Bg4 13. Qc1 $5
Bd7 $6 14. e5 $1 {
This position is shown on a stamp of the British Virgin Islands.} dxe5 15. Bxg6
fxg6 16. fxe5 O-O-O $2 {Black could move his knight instead.} 17. exf6 exf6 18.
Nge2 Bg4 19. Be3 Bxe2 20. Kxe2 Qb4 21. Re1 Bd6 22. h3 g5 23. Kf1 g4 24. hxg4 h5
25. g5 h4 26. Bf2 h3 27. gxh3 Rxh3 28. Re4 $2 Qa5 $2 (28... Rh1+ 29. Bg1 Bh2 {
counters.}) 29. Qd1 f5 30. Rh4 $5 Rxh4 31. Bxh4 Qb4 $5 32. Bf2 Qf4 33. Qh5 g6
34. Qh4 Qd2 35. Re1 Bf4 36. Rd1 Bxg5 37. Rxd2 Bxh4 {Hook had defeated a
competitor and Torre drew. So William won gold on board one by a score of 111/
2/14!} 1-0

